@amogelangostile3983 - Okay, so here we are a few months later, and this movie is considered a flop. Disney's estimated total losses are in the $70M-$80M range.
    Maybe you're confused by the term "box office gross", which does not equate to studio profits. The film cost $105M to make, and another $50+M in advertising/promotion costs. They need to make DOUBLE this in gross box office, as the theaters take half of the box office gross.
    So they were hoping to take a minimum of about $310M global box office... just to reach the break even point. They fell far short of that. They lost a ton of money.

