@merikano2985 Honestly I disagree with the Drinker in calling this movie a fundamentally flawed premise, I like the idea of a story from a Predator's perspective, I don't mind learning more of their culture (to an extent), I love the thought of them hunting something other than humans and somewhere other than Earth. You can reasonably have him find a broken down android and he uses it like a field guide.

BUT that's all contingent on good writing, they decided to go full blown Saturday morning cartoon with shit, neutering the Predator beyond recognition into this childhood hero. After seconds of hearing this bitch robot babble on nonstop, there's no way a self-respecting Predator wouldn't just crush her head or leave her for dead, especially after she seemingly betrayed him...they don't seem like the forgive and forget type when it involves dishonoring them.

You want to hear an unpopular opinion - I like the first Alien vs. Predator, not love it, but I enjoy it, that one also featured a Predator teaming up with a lady companion, even made her a makeshift spear and shield out of Xenomorph parts, that was handled alright.
